law.text:
As used in this chapter unless the context otherwise requires:
"Office" means the Office for the Blind;
"Legally blind" means a visual acuity of 20/200 or less in the better eye with correction or a visual field of 20 degrees or less;
"Visually impaired" means a condition of the eye with correction which constitutes or progressively results for the individual in a substantial disability to employment; and
"Executive director" means the executive director of the Office for the Blind.
